OWL té com a objectiu facilitar un model de marcat construït sobre RDF i codificat en XML. Té com a antecedent DAML+OIL, en els quals es van inspirar els creadors de OWL per crear el llenguatge. Al costat de l'entorn RDF i altres components, aquestes eines fan possible el projecte de web semàntica."@ca

questions.question: Where is the most deep point in the ocean?
questions.query: PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> PREFIX dct: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/> SELECT ?point WHERE { dbr:Extremes_on_Earth dct:subject ?x . ?point dct:subject ?x ; rdfs:comment ?comment FILTER ( lang(?comment) = "en" ) } OFFSET 47 LIMIT 1
triples: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/Line_parent> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A peak's line parent is the closest higher peak on the highest ridge leading away from the peak's "key col". A col is the lowest point on the ridge between two summits and is roughly synonymous with pass, gap, saddle and notch. The highest col of a peak is its key col. If there is more than one ridge which can be followed to a higher peak then the line parent is the peak closest to the key col. Usually, a line parent must meet some prominence criteria, which might vary depending on the author and the location of the peak."@en
